/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:2:This plugin unrestrict the Nvidia application clock command when an _exclusive job_ run on a node tagged with gres _nvgpufreq_.
/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:4:The nvgpufreq plugin call the _nvmlDeviceSetAPIRestriction()_ to restrict/unrestrict the GPU frequency clock at user level. When the application clock commands have been unrestricted a standard users can chenge the GPU frequency using the nvidia-smi tool or the NVML APIs.
/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:7:The nvgpufreq plugin intercepts the prolog and epilog of each job submitted in the cluster (_slurm_spank_job_prolog()_ and _slurm_spank_job_epilog()_).
/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:10:In the prolog procedure, the plugin does the following checks:
/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:13:2. Check if the node is tagged with the gres _nvgpufreq_. If the node is not tagged the plugin terminates its execution.
/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:15:4. Check if the job requests the nvgpufreq gres. If the job does not specify the gres _nvgpufreq_ the plugin terminates its execution.
/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:17:6. The plugin call the _nvmlDeviceSetAPIRestriction()_ to unrestrict the GPU frequency clock for regular users.
/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:20:In the epilog procedure, the plugin does the following checks:
/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:23:2. Check if the node is tagged with the gres _nvgpufreq_. If the node is not tagged the plugin terminates its execution.
/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:24:3. Check if the node has been configured from a nvgpufreq job and restore it. After that, the plugin deletes _/var/run/nvgpufreq.run_ and concludes the epilog procedure.
/data/users/chjing/slurm-nvgpufreq/README.md:27:To evaluate if the plugin concludes with the configuration of the node, the users/administrators can check the existence of the file _/var/run/nvgpufreq.run_, which contains the information if something when wrong or the plugin correctly terminated. This file should always be removed from the plugin in the epilog procedure after the restoration of the node.
